<h2><br/>
Complexity Theory’s 50-Year Journey to the Limits of Knowledge</h2>
<p>How hard is it to prove that problems are hard to solve? Meta-complexity theorists have been asking questions like this for decades. A string of recent results has started to deliver answers.</p>
